From: dgshue <dgshue@gmail.com>
Date: 2026-07-03
Subject: [PATCH] riscv: dts: spacemit: sync K1 board DTS from mainline master

Kernel 6.18 (OpenWrt stock) ships only a MINIMAL Orange Pi RV2 board DTS
(UART0 + LED). The K1 EMAC, MMC/SD, USB, PCIe and PMIC *drivers* are all
already present in 6.18 -- only the board-level device-tree WIRING that
enables them matured later (dual EMAC in 6.19-rc1; SD/USB/PCIe/PMIC in
mainline master heading to 6.19).

This patch replaces the in-tree 6.18 K1 SoC + board DTS with the mainline
master versions (verbatim, no local edits) so the router-critical set --
dual-GbE EMAC + microSD root + UART console -- is wired up on the 6.18
kernel. USB/PCIe nodes are also enabled by the master DTS but are treated
as phase-2 (their drivers/PHYs bind independently).

Files replaced (mainline master @ arch/riscv/boot/dts/spacemit/):
  k1.dtsi              870 -> 1345 lines  (adds eth0/eth1, sdhci0, emmc,
                                           usb_dwc3, usbphy2, pcie1/2,
                                           i2c8, pdma, qspi SoC nodes)
  k1-pinctrl.dtsi       79 ->  633 lines  (adds mmc1_cfg/mmc1_uhs_cfg,
                                           i2c8_cfg, qspi_cfg, pcie/usb
                                           pin groups -- REQUIRED: the
                                           6.18 RV2 SD node cannot resolve
                                           mmc1_cfg without this)
  k1-orangepi-rv2.dts   40 ->  386 lines  (enables dual EMAC + SD + USB +
                                           PCIe + P1 PMIC regulators)
  k1-bananapi-f3.dts    99 ->  396 lines  (kept consistent with new k1.dtsi)
  k1-milkv-jupiter.dts  79 ->  438 lines  (kept consistent with new k1.dtsi)

DELTA VALIDATION (6.18 vs master):
  - clock/reset macros: include/dt-bindings/clock/spacemit,k1-syscon.h is
    IDENTICAL between 6.18 and master (366 defines each) -> all CLK_*/RESET_*
    refs resolve.
  - all three K1 board DTS (rv2, bananapi-f3, milkv-jupiter) compile clean
    (cpp -> dtc, exit 0, zero warnings) against the 6.18 dt-bindings headers.
  - driver availability in 6.18 confirmed: SPACEMIT_K1_EMAC, MMC_SDHCI_OF_K1,
    SPACEMIT_CCU, RESET_SPACEMIT, PINCTRL(spacemit,k1-pinctrl), I2C_K1,
    MFD_SPACEMIT_P1, REGULATOR_SPACEMIT_P1.

Mainline authors of the DTS: Yangyu Chen <cyy@cyyself.name>,
Hendrik Hamerlinck <hendrik.hamerlinck@hammernet.be>. This is an OpenWrt
packaging patch that forward-ports their upstream work onto the 6.18 base;
it is upstreamable to the kernel only as "backport to stable", not as new
work. Flagged upstreamable; NOT to be submitted without approval.

Signed-off-by: dgshue <dgshue@gmail.com>
